balanceOf(address,uint256).details: See {IERC1155-balanceOf}. Requirements: - `account` cannot be the zero address.

balanceOfBatch(address[],uint256[]).details: See {IERC1155-balanceOfBatch}. Requirements: - `accounts` and `ids` must have the same length.

creatorOfToken(uint256).details: Gets the creator of the token

params._amount: amount of the token to delete

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

putOnSale(uint8,uint256,uint256,uint256,.details: update is for sale only from token Owner.

params._endTime: end time of bid, pass 0 of _priceType is not 1
params._startTime: start time of bid, pass 0 of _priceType is not 1

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

restore(address,uint256,uint256).details: restore data from old contract, only call by owner

setIsForSale(bool,uint256).details: update is for sale only from token Owner.

setMarketAddresses(address,address,addre.details: set marketAuction address to set the sale price

setPriceType(uint8,uint256).details: update price type from token Owner.

setTokenAmount(uint256,uint256).details: update or mint token Amount only from token creator.

supportsInterface(bytes4).details: See {IERC165-supportsInterface}. Time complexity O(1), guaranteed to always use less than 30 000 gas.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

uri(uint256).details: See {IERC1155MetadataURI-uri}. This implementation returns the same URI for *all* token types. It relies on the token type ID substitution mechanism https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-1155#metadata[defined in the EIP]. Clients calling this function must replace the `\{id\}` substring with the actual token type ID.
